The 50-year-old man is suspected to have overdosed on Viagra. [File, Standard]  A 50-year-old man died in Maragua Town, Murang’a County on Wednesday, July 28 due to a suspected Viagra overdose.  Fredrick Opiyo was reported to have died a few minutes past midnight.  Police say Opiyo booked himself into a Maragua Town lodging with his lover, 35, on Tuesday night.  “He arrived at Rurago Bar a few minutes past 9pm. He took supper and was later, at 10pm, joined by a youthful woman. The two, thereafter, went to a guest room that Opiyo had booked,” Murang’a South Sub-County Police Commander Alexander Shikondi told The Standard.  Female viagra gets approval but with strong health warning  Officials seize Chinese spirits laced with Viagra  Research: How women can help men satisfy their bedroom needs  'Female Viagra' gets green light from US expert panel According to Opiyo’s lover, the man complained of chest pains shortly after taking a bath.  “The woman said that upon entering the room, Opiyo went into the bathroom and took a shower. After he was done, she also entered the bathroom for a shower. It was during bath that she heard Opiyo groaning on bed. She rushed out and found Opiyo struggling for breath,” said Shikondi.  The woman is said to have immediately alerted the guest room’s security guard caretaker.  On accessing the room, the staff members found Opiyo had already died.  Police recovered one used condom, two unopened ones and an empty Viagra pack.  Opiyo’s body was taken to Murang’a County Hospital mortuary, awaiting postmortem.  “We will question witnesses, including the woman and the guest room staff,” said Shikondi.   This is the celebrity who overdosed on herbal Viagra  This is the celebrity who overdosed on herbal Viagra  Shehena ya dawa ghushi za kuongeza nguvu za kiume zapatikana Nairobi By Phares Mutembei | 1 day ago By Muriithi Mugo | 2 days ago By Biketi Kikechi | 3 days ago By Fidelis Kabunyi | 3 days ago